body:
## How to introduce Buildkite into Blueoil CI
At first, I try to introduce Buildkite without breaking changes of current CI settings, and take a parallel period with Jenkins and Buildkite for verification of CI settings.

Now I am developing the environment and some changes to tests of Blueoil according to follow steps.
- [x] Separate some tests for speed up without breaking change #340 #356 
- [x] Fix unstable tests to improve CI quality # #325 #351
- [x] Add buildkite pipeline settings #357

issue.body:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1946823/54104588-c6affb00-4413-11e9-9b9f-15e6db6bc6c3.png)

Now it takes 20~30min for each tasks in https://jenkins.blue-oil.org and they are not allowed to run in concurrently.

This should be at least allowed to be concurrent. This requires managing docker tags correctly.
